{
  "stem": "71.3",
  "chunk_idx": 2,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 8.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "When she left us and went with our little sister-- [PAUSES FOR 13 SECONDS] she knew she wouldn't be able to-- to live all by herself, she was too young.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] I'm just very sad that my mother didn't go with us.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "She could have lived probably another few years.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "But then this was her-- her way of showing that she loved us, and she loved my little sister.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 8 SECONDS]",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, I--",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I think that I took the blame for them not coming with us because later as I looked at it, I said, if I would not have cut it-- maybe Samson had his hair cut off, and I took the power away from them.",
      "word_count": 44
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "[CRYING]",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I know that.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I'm trying to tell myself many-- many sleepless nights that I had-- that I tried my best at the time, that what I understood to do.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "If I would not have do it, maybe-- maybe they would shave their heads.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "They shaved them anyway, but we-- we did not know at that time.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I just wanted to save the shame of being without hair.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "For a woman, it's a very, very drastic thing to-- to bear.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Because when-- when we were in Auschwitz, and we were staying outside and was a group of women, and one of the girl-- of the girls that walked with me in the ghetto said, I hear Sally's voice but I don't know where she is.",
      "word_count": 45
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "She's just standing right there looking in my face, but she did not recognize me.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And when I went out once from a barrack, and there was a little window, passing by was like a dark little corridor, and there was a window.",
      "word_count": 28
    }
  ],
